===Etymology===
Originally verb sense “drink heartily”, from {{etyl|enm}} {{term|bibben|lang=enm}}, either from {{etyl|la}} {{term|bibo|bibō|I drink|lang=la}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|peh₃-}}, or of imitative origin {{onomatopoeia}}. Noun sense (clothing) presumably either because worn while drinking, or because the clothing itself “drinks up” spills.<ref>{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

